.TH NET-MGR 7 "2026-04-29" "net-mgr" "net-mgr"
.SH NAME
net-mgr \- network observation broker and tools overview
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B net-mgr
is a Perl daemon plus a set of CLI tools that maintain a MySQL/MariaDB-backed
inventory of every device on the local network: machines, interfaces, IP
addresses, listening ports, WiFi access points, client associations, and DHCP
leases. The daemon is the only process that writes to the database. Producers
push observations to it over a line-based TCP protocol; consumers subscribe
to live updates over the same socket.
.SH ARCHITECTURE
Three roles:
.IP \(bu 2
.B Daemon \fR(\fBnet-mgr\fR(8), \fBnet-dns\fR(8), \fBnet-mgr-relay\fR(8)) \(em
listens on 127.0.0.1:7531, owns the DB, dispatches OBSERVE messages, fires
events on transitions.
.IP \(bu 2
.B Producers \fR(\fBnet-discover\fR(1), \fBnet-poll-ap\fR(1),
\fBnet-import-dhcp\fR(1), \fBnet-ping\fR(1)) \(em scan or poll the network
and push observations.
.IP \(bu 2
.B Consumers \fR(\fBnet-scan\fR(1), \fBnet-show\fR(1), \fBnet-report\fR(1),
\fBnet-watch\fR(1), \fBnet-roam\fR(1)) \(em snapshot tables or stream events
without writing.
.SH TYPICAL WORKFLOWS
.SS Survey the network
.nf
.RS 4
net-scan                # known hosts
net-show                # APs and SSIDs
net-report aps          # raw aps table
.RE
.fi
.SS Add a new fixed-IP host
.nf
.RS 4
net-fix --mac aa:bb:cc:dd:ee:ff --name printer
fix_dhcp                # regenerate dhcpd.conf
.RE
.fi
.SS Investigate a flaky connection
.nf
.RS 4
net-watch 192.168.15.42         # live RTT/loss for one IP
net-report events \\
  "type IN ('interface_online','interface_offline') AND mac = 'aa:bb:..'"
.RE
.fi
.SS Push roaming clients off weak APs
.nf
.RS 4
net-roam --list                 # who's being watched
net-roam --dry-run --verbose    # what would be kicked
net-roam                        # do it
.RE
.fi
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/net-mgr/config
Daemon and tool configuration. See
.BR net-mgr (8).
.TP
.I /etc/net-mgr/dhcp.master
Hand-curated authoritative DHCP reservations. Imported via
.BR net-import-dhcp (1).
.TP
.I /var/log/net-mgr.log
Daemon log.
.TP
.I /var/cache/net-mgr/
Per-tool state caches (AP poll backoff, fingerprint results).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR net-alias (1),
.BR net-discover (1),
.BR net-fix (1),
.BR net-import-dhcp (1),
.BR net-ping (1),
.BR net-poll-ap (1),
.BR net-report (1),
